<section class="hero container fade-up">
  <p class="t-eyebrow hero__eyebrow">Framework 08 · A return</p>
  <h1 class="t-h1 hero__title t-balance">Awakening Into Humanity</h1>
  <p class="t-lead hero__lead t-pretty">Not out of life. Into it. A return rather than an escape.</p>
</section>

<section class="section section--sunk fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid-2" style="align-items:center; gap: var(--sp-8);">
      <div class="fw-art">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 280" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M 40 220 Q 200 30 360 220" fill="none" stroke="var(--c-accent)" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        <path d="M 40 220 Q 200 70  360 220" fill="none" stroke="var(--c-accent)" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.5"/>
        <line x1="40" y1="220" x2="360" y2="220" stroke="var(--c-line)" stroke-width="0.6"/>
        <g fill="var(--c-accent)">
          <circle cx="40"  cy="220" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="360" cy="220" r="4"/>
        </g>
        <circle cx="200" cy="86" r="5" fill="var(--c-accent-soft)" stroke="var(--c-accent)" stroke-width="1"/>
        <g font-family="var(--font-body)" font-size="11" letter-spacing="0.22em" fill="var(--c-ink-mute)">
          <text x="40"  y="248" text-anchor="middle">OUT</text>
          <text x="360" y="248" text-anchor="middle">IN</text>
        </g>
      </svg></div>
      <div class="stack-lg">
        <p class="t-lead t-pretty">Much of what is called awakening teaches us to rise out of the human — to transcend, to detach, to view from above. There is something in this. There is also a great forgetting; a leaving behind of the very body that was supposed to be saved.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">Awakening into humanity is the opposite direction. It is the slow consent to come back down — into the body, into the relationships, into the messiness of being a person inside the world. To be here on purpose, not by accident.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">It does not feel like enlightenment. It feels like grief, and tenderness, and the strange relief of being finally allowed to be here.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section fade-up">
  <div class="container narrow center-text">
    <p class="pull t-balance"><em>You do not awaken out of being human. You awaken into it.</em></p>
  </div>
</section>

